==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[ζευγμα]]'' (zeugma).

===Pronunciation===
* [[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|IPA]]: /zugmə/ ''or'' /zjugmə/

===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|Zeugma}}
'''zeugma''' (''plural:'' '''[[zeugmata]]''')
# The act of using a word, particularly an adjective or verb, to apply to more than one noun when its sense is appropriate to only one or in different ways; as a rhetorical measure, it is fun: it's a clever abuse of a verb or adverb; puns are also included.

===Synonyms===
* [[Syllepsis]]

===Example===
<b>He slipped on his jacket and a banana peel out the door.</b>
One can slip on a jacket and also slip on a banana peel, but here the verb is happily agreed, and yes, this is fun English.


